I've implemented my game class and it works so far. Now I want to prevent the user from resizing the game window and closing it using ALT+F4. In the constructor of the game class, I added the following lines:

``` csharp
public Game1()
{
    graphics = new GraphicsDeviceManager(this);
    Content.RootDirectory = "Content";
    graphics.PreferredBackBufferWidth = 600;
    graphics.PreferredBackBufferHeight = 400;
    Window.Title = "BirdAttack";
    Window.AllowAltF4 = false;
    Window.AllowUserResizing = false;
}
```

The game starts and all routines are working but I am still able to resize the window individually and close it using the combination. Putting these lines in the **Initialize**-method hasn't been working, too.
Am I doing something wrong or is this an issue in MonoGame?

Hi all,

I've noticed an issue with SpriteBatch rendering on WindowsGL platform (does not occur on Windows DX nor XNA 4.0). When drawing a sprite that moves at constant speed, the animation "stutters" and is not smooth, even though the program runs at 60fps. It seems that sometimes the draw is delaye or something.

Here's a very simple example to reproduce the bug (the texture red is just a 64x64 red texture):

``` C#
using Microsoft.Xna.Framework;
using Microsoft.Xna.Framework.Graphics;
using Microsoft.Xna.Framework.Input;

namespace MonogameTest
{
    public class Game1 : Game
    {
        public Game1()
        {
            _graphics = new GraphicsDeviceManager(this);
            Content.RootDirectory = "Content";
            IsFixedTimeStep = true;
        }

        ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////// Override Methods

        protected override void LoadContent()
        {
            _spriteBatch = new SpriteBatch(GraphicsDevice);
            _texture = Content.Load<Texture2D>("red");
            _pos = Point.Zero;
        }

        protected override void Update(GameTime gameTime)
        {
            if (Keyboard.GetState().IsKeyDown(Keys.Space))
            {
                _pos.X = 0;
            }
            _pos.X += 6;

            base.Update(gameTime);
        }

        protected override void Draw(GameTime gameTime)
        {
            GraphicsDevice.Clear(Color.CornflowerBlue);

            _spriteBatch.Begin();
            _spriteBatch.Draw(_texture, _pos.ToVector2(), Color.White);
            _spriteBatch.End();

            base.Draw(gameTime);
        }

        ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////// Private Members

        private GraphicsDeviceManager _graphics;
        private SpriteBatch _spriteBatch;
        private Texture2D _texture;
        private Point _pos;

    }
}
```

I've reproduced it Monogame 3.4 and also with the last unstable version (currently 3.5.0.703). I also tried on 2 different computers, same problem with both.

Thanks in advance!

Martin

Added Conditions to handle the case where there are no content files.
Also added a conditional so we don't error
